lead_paragraph: Carlos Brathwaite shone briefly for West Indies but the rain was the only real winner on Monday as wet weather washed away all but 11.2 overs of play on the second day of the third test against Australia.

headline.print_headline: Brathwaite Cameo a Bright Spot in Sydney Washout
